{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"085d2251-2a86-46fb-8b8e-00b9d88d362c","content":"In .NET 10 MAUI, the iOS-specific `UseSafeArea` attached property was replaced with a **cross-platform `SafeAreaRegions` property** directly on `Page`.\n\n**Old (.NET 9):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage\n    xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n    ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"\n    ...>\n```\n\n**New (.NET 10):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage\n    SafeAreaRegions=\"All\"\n    ...>\n```\n\nYou can drop the `xmlns:ios` declaration entirely if it was only used for `UseSafeArea`.\n\nThe `SafeAreaRegions` property is a flags enum, so you can also be selective:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Only respect safe area at top and bottom -->\n<ContentPage SafeAreaRegions=\"Top,Bottom\">\n```\n\nAvailable values: `None`, `All`, `Top`, `Bottom`, `Left`, `Right`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5c8b9799-5de0-4a46-abca-b4fcda082442","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI migration issue from .NET 9 to .NET 10 regarding safe area handling on iOS. This is a known breaking change in .NET 10 MAUI.\n\nIn .NET 10, the `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` attached property was removed/deprecated. The replacement is to use the new `SafeAreaRegions` property on `Page` (or individual layout controls).\n\nLet me provide the correct answer based on my knowledge of .NET MAUI .NET 10 changes.\n\nIn .NET 10 MAUI, `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` was replaced with a cross-platform `Page.SafeAreaRegions` property. \n\nThe new `SafeAreaRegions` is a flags enum that accepts values like `All`, `None`, `Top`, `Bottom`, `Left`, and `Right`, giving you more granular control over which edges respect the safe area. This property works directly on the `ContentPage` without needing an iOS-specific namespace.","outputTokens":689,"requestId":"E82C:21DC3D:2661F87:2A8D536:69F942A4"},"id":"2cac6462-f24c-4722-9c75-2d893eeefa14","timestamp":"2026-05-0